articles.author: JOSEF FEDERMAN and ISSAM ADWAN
articles.description: JERUSALEM (AP) — Israel bombarded downtown Gaza City on Tuesday and expanded a massive mobilization of reservists, vowing punishing retaliation against the Hamas militant group that increasingly left residents of the tiny Palestinian territory with nowhere to go.
articles.title: Israel pounds downtown Gaza City, vowing punishing retaliation for weekend attack

articles.author: AAMER MADHANI and ELLEN KNICKMEYER
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Less than three weeks ago, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu sat beside President Joe Biden and marveled that a “historic peace between Israel and Saudi Arabia” seemed within reach — a diplomatic advance that he predicted could lead to lasting peace between the Israelis and Palestinians.
articles.title: Biden's hopes for establishing Israel-Saudi relations could become a casualty of the new Mideast war

articles.author: DARLENE SUPERVILLE and ERIC TUCKER
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — President Joe Biden has been interviewed as part of an independent investigation into his handling of classified documents, the White House said late Monday.
articles.title: Biden interviewed as part of special counsel investigation into handling of classified documents

articles.author: MICHAEL R. SISAK
articles.description: NEW YORK (AP) — As Donald Trump’s longtime finance chief, Allen Weisselberg helped spare the former president’s real estate empire from its last existential threat, staving off insolvency after casino bankruptcies and an airline failure in the 1990s.
articles.title: Donald Trump’s civil fraud trial is resuming with ex-CFO Allen Weisselberg on the witness stand

articles.author: EBRAHIM NOROOZI and OMID HAQJO
articles.description: ZINDA JAN, Afghanistan (AP) — Clinging to hope that finding survivors was still possible, Afghan rescuers and villagers kept digging through rubble in western Herat province on Tuesday, three days after one of the deadliest earthquakes in the region left more than 2,000 dead.
articles.title: Afghans still hope to find survivors from quake that killed over 2,000 in western Herat province

articles.author: BRIAN SLODYSKO
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Charlie Kirk’s $4.75 million Spanish-style estate is tucked away in a gated Arizona country club that charges nearly a half-million dollars for a golf membership. It boasts a guest casita, “resort-style” pool and striking views of the Sonoran Desert.
articles.title: How Trump's MAGA movement helped a 29-year-old activist become a millionaire

articles.description: SAN FRANCISCO (AP) — A car rammed into the Chinese consulate in San Francisco on Monday, coming to a stop in the lobby and creating a chaotic scene that ended with police shooting the driver, who later died at the hospital, officials said.
articles.title: Car rams into Chinese consulate in San Francisco and police fatally shoot driver, officers say

articles.author: PAUL WISEMAN and DAVID McHUGH
articles.description: The world economy has lost momentum from the impact of higher interest rates, the invasion of Ukraine and widening geopolitical rifts, and it now faces new uncertainty from the war between Israel and Hamas militants, International Monetary Fund warned Tuesday.
articles.title: IMF outlook worsens for a 'limping' world economy. Mideast war poses new uncertainty

articles.description: TORONTO (AP) — Auto workers walked off the job at three General Motors facilities in Canada early Tuesday after failing to reach agreement with the automaker. Their union, Unifor, represents more than 4,200 workers at the plants.
articles.title: Auto workers begin strike at GM plants in Canada, as talks continue
